## Phased Implementation Roadmap

### Phase 1 – Foundation

1. Read [01-architecture-overview.mdc](01-architecture-overview.mdc) and map it to DAGs you plan to build under `src/dags`.
2. Skim [09-config-and-deployment.mdc](09-config-and-deployment.mdc) for Airflow, S3, SQS, and environment setup.

### Phase 2 – Ingestion & Bronze (Crawl + Raw Storage)

3. Implement or update ingestion per [02-ingestion-layer.mdc](02-ingestion-layer.mdc):
   - **Link discovery**: Homepage and key sections → push URLs to SQS.
   - **Workers**: Multiple tasks pull from SQS, fetch HTML, and write to S3 bronze.
4. Store raw HTML snapshots in bronze S3 using [03-raw-storage-bronze.mdc](03-raw-storage-bronze.mdc) conventions.

### Phase 3 – Silver (LLM Gemini + Parsing)

5. Design silver schemas in [04-transform-silver.mdc](04-transform-silver.mdc) (article metadata: title, section, publish time, summary, entities, etc.).
6. Implement silver transform: read bronze HTML from S3, call **Gemini** to extract structured fields from HTML, validate and normalize output, deduplicate by article ID, write Parquet to S3 silver.

### Phase 4 – Gold & Analytics – Optional

7. Define gold outputs in [05-analytics-gold-clickhouse.mdc](05-analytics-gold-clickhouse.mdc): tables for article analytics (by section, time, topic) or search-friendly stores.
8. Ensure gold steps produce stable S3 or database locations for downstream jobs (dashboards, search indexers, ML).

### Phase 5 – Quality & Advanced

9. Add tests and data-quality checks per [07-data-quality-and-testing.mdc](07-data-quality-and-testing.mdc).
10. Use [10-advanced-patterns.mdc](10-advanced-patterns.mdc) for backfills, schema evolution, and scaling the crawler (more sections, higher frequency).

## Common Workflows

### Adding a New Section or URL Pattern

1. Update link-discovery logic and configuration in [02-ingestion-layer.mdc](02-ingestion-layer.mdc) (e.g. list of section URLs, allowed path patterns).
2. Ensure bronze S3 layout remains compatible or document any changes in [03-raw-storage-bronze.mdc](03-raw-storage-bronze.mdc).
3. If you parse content, update silver (Gemini prompts and schema) in [04-transform-silver.mdc](04-transform-silver.mdc) to include section/category or new fields.

### Changing Crawl Frequency or Depth

1. Adjust Airflow DAG schedules using [06-airflow-dags.mdc](06-airflow-dags.mdc) as a guide.
2. Tune SQS batch sizes and worker concurrency to match new load.
3. Revisit data-retention and analytics needs in [05-analytics-gold-clickhouse.mdc](05-analytics-gold-clickhouse.mdc).
